## Example 8 — Identify Transformations

For each graph, identify the value of [k] and write the function in terms of [f(x) = \log_5 x].

### Step 1: Analyze [g(x) = f(x) + k]

If the graph is shifted vertically, [k] represents the vertical shift. Compare key points on the graph to [f(x)] to determine [k].

### Step 2: Analyze [h(x) = k \cdot f(x)]

If the graph is stretched or compressed vertically, [k] represents the vertical stretch factor.

### Step 3: Analyze [j(x) = f(x) + k]

Similar to [g(x)], identify the vertical shift from the graph's position relative to [f(x)].

